      • createProcess

        protected abstract Process createProcess()
                                  throws ProcessException
        Abstract method that must be provided by implementations to create a process instance from the definition. This method is declared protected because it should only be invoked by the process manager. Therefore subclasses should leave the access modifier as "protected".
        Returns:
        The new process instance
        Throws:
        ProcessException - If creating the new instance fails
